article.description: Felix Von Hofe made seven of Eastern Washington's 15 3-pointers and finished with a career-high 25 points to help the Eagles beat Seattle 76-70 on Wednesday.
article.headline: Von Hofe makes 7 3's, Eastern Washington beats Seattle 76-70
article.linkText: Von Hofe makes 7 3's, Eastern Washington beats Seattle 76-70
article.story: CHENEY, Wash. -- Felix Von Hofe made seven of Eastern Washington's 15 3-pointers and finished with a career-high 25 points to help the Eagles beat Seattle 76-70 on Wednesday. Eastern Washington built a 68-53 lead with 5:27 left but Seattle made three consecutive 3-pointers during an 11-0 run to make it 68-64. The Eagles sealed it by making 6 of 8 free throws in the final minute. Austin McBroom hit four 3-pointers and had 16 points for Eastern Washington (2-1). Sir Washington added 11 points and Bogdan Bliznyuk 10. Brendan Westendorf made four 3-pointers and scored 20 points to lead Seattle (0-3). Jadon Cohee added 11 points and Jack Crook had 10. The Redhawks made 9 of 15 3-pointers. The game was originally scheduled for Tuesday night, but a windstorm across Eastern Washington created dangerous travel conditions.
